<!-- Card 1: What is a BEP --><div style="border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:16px;background:#ffffff;padding:18px;">
<div style="font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:#0e1e3d;margin-bottom:8px;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">What is a BEP?</span></div>
<div style="color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;">The <strong>BIM Execution Plan (BEP)</strong> explains how the project team will <strong>deliver information in response to the EIR</strong>. It sets out the processes, standards, responsibilities, and delivery approach that will be followed to produce, coordinate, review, and verify information throughout the project lifecycle.</div>
</div>
<!-- Card 2: Who is this for --><div style="margin-top:12px;border:1px solid #e8eef6;border-radius:16px;background:#ffffff;padding:18px;">
<div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:800;color:#0e1e3d;margin-bottom:8px;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Who is this for?</span></div>
<ul style="margin:0 0 0 18px;color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;">
<li>
<strong>Lead Appointed Parties</strong> responsible for coordinating information delivery</li>
<li>
<strong>Task Teams</strong> producing models, data, and documentation</li>
<li>
<strong>Information Managers</strong> overseeing compliance with the EIR</li>
</ul>
</div>
<!-- Note: Assignment use --><div style="margin-top:12px;background:#fbfdff;border:1px solid #dbe6f3;border-left:5px solid #009ef5;border-radius:14px;padding:14px 16px;"><div style="min-width:0;">
<div style="font-weight:700;color:#1c2430;margin-bottom:6px;font-size:14px;">Note (assignment use)</div>
<div style="color:#5b6b88;line-height:1.65;font-size:14px;">
<p>This BEP template is <strong>pre-filled as a realistic project example</strong>. Your task is to review each section below and complete the highlighted <strong>Smart Fields</strong> so that the BEP clearly responds to the EIR you created in Task 1.</p>
<p>Focus on aligning the delivery approach, responsibilities, and processes with the defined information requirements.</p>
</div>
